@page "/counter"
@* page URL, (?directive? (uncertain if thats the right term)) *@
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@* ties into render mode takes events and deals with them server side*@

<PageTitle>Counter</PageTitle>

<h1>Counter</h1>

<p role="status">Current count: @currentCount</p>
@* csharp code denoted by the at sign, calling the currentCount variable that exists in the csharp code

can demarcate the code with () , eg @(currentCount)*@

<button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="IncrementCount">Click me</button>
@* increment count being called from the code which runs the code and increments the count and updates the variable in real time 
    dont need to call a method, you can program right in the statement eg @onclick="() => currentCount++"
*@

@code {
    private int currentCount = 0;

    [Parameter] //User caan give the variable any value we want
    public int IncrementAmmount { get; set; } = 1;
    @*Allowing different increment amounts on different pages*@

    private void IncrementCount()
    {
        currentCount += IncrementAmmount;
    }
}
